+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015hUWzvMVuTyL1eZZWCibjU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've successfully explored the codebase and gathered all the requested information. Here's a comprehensive overview:\n\n## Codebase Structure Overview\n\nThe project is a Notes application with full-text search capabilities built with TypeScript, Express, and SQLite (better-sqlite3).\n\n### Project Structure\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── db.ts          (database setup and seeding)\n│   ├── models.ts      (TypeScript interfaces)\n│   ├── routes.ts      (Express routes for CRUD)\n│   ├── errors.ts      (custom error classes)\n│   ├── server.ts      (Express app setup)\n│   └── seed.ts        (seeding script)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── search.test.ts (20 search-related tests)\n│   └── notes.test.ts  (15 CRUD tests)\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n└── vitest.config.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n## Detailed File Contents\n\n### 1. `/workspace/package.json`\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-fts-search\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Full-text search feature benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"seed\": \"tsx src/seed.ts\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.0.0\",\n    \"express\": \"^4.21.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/better-sqlite3\": \"^7.6.0\",\n    \"@types/express\": \"^4.17.0\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/supertest\": \"^6.0.0\",\n    \"tsx\": \"^4.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `/workspace/src/db.ts`\nComplete database setup with 50 seed notes covering diverse topics:\n\n- **`createDatabase(path?: string)`** - Creates SQLite database with WAL mode, creates notes table with columns: id, title, body, tags (JSON), created_at, updated_at\n- **`seedDatabase(db)`** - Inserts 50 predefined notes into the database\n- **`getSeedNotes()`** - Returns array of 50 seed notes with tags including:\n  - Programming topics (TypeScript, Python, Rust, React, Docker, Kubernetes, GraphQL, etc.)\n  - Cooking/Food (pasta, cookies, risotto, Thai food, sourdough, espresso, etc.)\n  - Travel (Tokyo, Paris, Kilimanjaro, Southeast Asia, hiking, etc.)\n  - Science/Tech (quantum computing, AI, machine learning, blockchain, etc.)\n  - Health/Wellness (meditation, yoga, sleep, nutrition, etc.)\n  - Arts/Culture (photography, music, classical music, painting, chess, etc.)\n  - And more...\n\n---\n\n### 3. `/workspace/src/models.ts`\n```typescript\nexport interface Note {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags: string; // JSON array as string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface NoteInput {\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n}\n\nexport interface SearchResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  snippet: string;\n  rank: number;\n}\n\nexport interface SuggestResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `/workspace/src/routes.ts`\nImplements CRUD endpoints:\n\n- **`GET /notes`** - List all notes (with optional `?tag=X` filter using json_each)\n- **`GET /notes/:id`** - Get single note by ID\n- **`POST /notes`** - Create note (validates title and body, returns 201)\n- **`PUT /notes/:id`** - Update note (partial updates, updates timestamp)\n- **`DELETE /notes/:id`** - Delete note (returns 204)\n\n---\n\n### 5. `/workspace/src/errors.ts`\n```typescript\nexport class NotFoundError extends Error {\n  statusCode = 404;\n  constructor(message = 'Resource not found')\n}\n\nexport class ValidationError extends Error {\n  statusCode = 400;\n  constructor(message = 'Validation failed')\n}\n\nexport function errorHandler(err, _req, res, _next): void {\n  // Handles NotFoundError (404), ValidationError (400), other errors (500)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `/workspace/src/server.ts`\n```typescript\nexport interface App {\n  app: express.Express;\n  db: Database.Database;\n}\n\nexport function createApp(dbPath?: string): App\nexport function createSeededApp(dbPath?: string): App\n```\n- Creates Express app with JSON middleware\n- Sets up routes and error handler\n- `createSeededApp()` additionally runs seedDatabase\n\n---\n\n### 7. `/workspace/src/seed.ts`\nSimple script that:\n- Accepts optional database path (default: `notes.db`)\n- Creates and seeds database\n- Logs count of seeded notes\n- Closes database connection\n\n---\n\n### 8. `/workspace/tests/search.test.ts` - 20 Search Tests\nExpects a full-text search feature with these endpoints:\n\n**GET /notes/search**\n1. Returns matching notes with `?q=keyword` parameter\n2. Results have `snippet` field (highlighted matching terms)\n3. Snippets contain `<mark>` tags around matched terms\n4. Results ranked by relevance (ascending rank values)\n5. Supports exact phrase queries: `?q=\"exact phrase\"`\n6. Returns objects with: `id`, `title`, `snippet`, `rank`\n7. Returns empty array for non-existent terms\n8. Returns 400 without `?q` parameter\n9. Returns 400 with empty `?q=`\n\n**Pagination**\n10. `?page=1` returns first 20 results, response includes `page`, `perPage`\n11. `?page=2` returns next results\n12. Response includes `total` count of all matches\n\n**GET /notes/search/suggest**\n13. `?q=prefix` returns up to 5 title suggestions\n14. Results match prefix in title\n15. Returns 400 with empty `?q=`\n\n**FTS Synchronization**\n16. New notes appear in search immediately\n17. Updated notes reflect changes in search\n18. Deleted notes disappear from search\n\n**Robustness**\n19. Special characters in query don't crash (spaces, &, ', <>, +, /)\n20. Search response time under 100ms for seeded dataset\n\n---\n\n### 9. `/workspace/tests/notes.test.